How to translate "wandering mind"?
by Asia » Mon 11.14.2011 3:00 pm Im trying to figure out how to say "wandering mind" in Japanese/romaji (its for a youtube account). Im still just learning and I dont know enough to translate it myself, so Ive been having to use google translator ( ) and a friend who knows a little Japanese. (Though I did use a couple other translators, but I got the same results)Anyway, when I first translated it I got さまよう心 (Samayō kokoro). Said friend didnt know if Samayo was the correct word for "wandering", but she was pretty sure kokoro meant "mind". Except when I looked it up, and used the translator, it said kokoro actually meant "heart". So then I decided to translate the words seperatly I got 放浪 (Hōrō) for "wandering" and 注意 (Chūi) for "mind" Then theres the sentence structure. I know in Japanese the subject is at the beginning, the verb is at the end, and the object is in the middle. So in Japanese would it actually be "mind wandering"?I probably sound like a total idiot, but any help would be appreciated! Asia
