Re: How to translate "wandering mind"?
by Asia » Mon 11.14.2011 5:57 pm I found an old Japanese to English dictionary that I had gotten from the library a while back, it says kokoro means "heart; mind; spirit; feeling". But for chui it says "attention; caution; warning". Asia
