Re: How to translate "wandering mind"?
by SomeCallMeChris » Mon 11.14.2011 7:00 pm Actually, thinking about what I just said, I might suggest you find a native speaker of Japanese and see how they feel about さまよってる想像 = 'wandering imagination'. Sounds clumsy in English, but I -think- it sounds good in Japanese. I'm not a native speaker though and have never tried the phrase.
